Any person who, without lawful right or authority—
(a) alters, enlarges or obstructs any works , or destroys, defaces or moves any level marks, beacons or other structure or appliance erected or made in conjunction with such works ;
alters, enlarges or obstructs any works , or destroys, defaces or moves any level marks, beacons or other structure or appliance erected or made in conjunction with such works ;
(b) takes for purposes other than primary use , any public water , unless authorised in terms of this Act or in the exercise of a legal right existing at the commencement of this Act;
